org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.lock
Class AeLockRequest

java.lang.Object
  org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.lock.AeLockRequest
Direct Known Subclasses:
AeExclusiveLockRequest, AeSharedLockRequest
public abstract class AeLockRequest
extends java.lang.Object

Describes the request for a variable locking. The request is executed through the acquireLock() method. If the lock is able to be acquired immediately then lock holders will be installed for the locked variables. If not, then the request is added to the failed request collection in the outter class for an attempt at a later time.

acquireLock

protected boolean acquireLock()
Template method that dictates the structure of acquiring a lock. First we see if it's possible to lock all of the variables in question. If so, the locks are added otherwise we add ourselves to the failed requests collection.

addLockHolders

protected void addLockHolders()
Walks the set of variables to lock and adds the owner as a lock holder for each of the variables. If there is no lock holder installed for the variable then one is created.
